        <h2 id="recipe-1" class="recipe"> Pancake</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 20 minutes</li>
            <li>Serves: 2</li>
        </ul>
        
                <img id="1st-image" class="image" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/43/Blueberry_pancakes_%283%29.jpg/220px-Blueberry_pancakes_%283%29.jpg" alt="pancake">
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>No.</th>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>1.</td>
                    <td>Flour</td>
                    <td>1 ½ cups </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>2.</td>
                    <td>Baking powder</td>
                    <td>3 ½ teaspoons</td>
                    
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>3.</td>
                    <td>salt</td>
                    <td>1 teaspoon</td>
                
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>4.</td>
                    <td>white sugar</td>
                    <td>1 teaspoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>5.</td>
                    <td>cups milk</td>
                    <td>1 ¼ cups</td>
                    
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>6.</td>
                    <td>egg</td>
                    <td>1</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>7.</td>
                    <td>butter, melted</td>
                    <td>3 tablespoons</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> In a large bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Make a well in the center and pour in the milk, egg and melted butter; mix until smooth.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Step 2:</strong> Heat a lightly oiled griddle or frying pan over medium-high heat. Pour or scoop the batter onto the griddle, using approximately 1/4 cup for each pancake. Brown on both sides and serve hot.
</p>

